The paper deals with the problem of identifying a linear operator from input-output measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and control theory. The use of compressive sensing techniques is also mentioned in the abstract. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses stability and identifiability, which are topics in cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with the spreading function of the operator, which is a concept in cs.SP (Signal Processing).
